# Architecture

## The Hard Boundary: Expendable Layer vs Engine Room

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  EXPENDABLE LAYER (can be killed by Android OS) │
│  Jetpack Compose UI, MapLibre Renderer,         │
│  HUD Zones 1-3, Detour Voting Overlays          │
│  → Only OBSERVES state via StateFlow/Flow       │
│  → Never writes to DB or calls network directly │
└──────────────────┬──────────────────────────────┘
                   │ observes StateFlow
┌──────────────────▼──────────────────────────────┐
│  ENGINE ROOM (ConvoyForegroundService)          │
│  Must survive: screen off, battery saver,       │
│  OEM task killers, Android Doze                 │
│                                                  │
│  • BatchedLocationManager (GPS)                 │
│  • CrashDetectionManager (IMU + SOS)            │
│  • ConvoyMeshManager (P2P + BLE)                │
│  • AudioRouteManager (SCO/TTS)                  │
│  • RouteForecaster + GripMatrix (weather)       │
│  • SignalRecoveryReceiver (dead-zone beacon)    │
│  • BatterySurvivalManager (OperationalState)    │
│  • Room + SQLCipher (encrypted local DB)        │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Hilt DI Modules

- `AppModule` -- Singleton-scoped: `SlickDatabase`, `SupabaseClient`, `OpenMeteoService`, `SecurePayloadManager`
- `ServiceModule` -- Service-scoped: `BatchedLocationManager`, `ConvoyMeshManager`, `AudioRouteManager`
- `DataModule` -- DAOs, repositories, `RouteRepository`

Never inject Service-scoped components into Application-scoped singletons.

## Package Structure

```
com.slick.tactical/
  app/                        SlickApplication.kt (Hilt entry)
  di/                         AppModule, ServiceModule, DataModule
  service/
    ConvoyForegroundService   Lifecycle owner for Engine Room
    BatterySurvivalManager    PowerManager + OperationalState flow
    GarageSyncWorker          WorkManager: PMTiles delta updates
  engine/
    location/                 BatchedLocationManager
    imu/                      CrashDetectionManager
    mesh/                     ConvoyMeshManager, ConvoyLeaderManager,
                              ConvoyOptimizationManager
    audio/                    AudioRouteManager
    weather/                  RouteForecaster, GripMatrix,
                              TwilightMatrix, SolarGlareVector
    signal/                   SignalRecoveryReceiver
    haven/                    EmergencyHavenLocator
    crypto/                   SecurePayloadManager
    health/                   DeviceHealthManager
  data/
    local/                    SlickDatabase, DAOs, entities
    remote/                   SupabaseClient, OpenMeteoClient,
                              OverpassClient, ValhallClient
    proto/                    .proto schemas
    model/                    Domain models (Route, WeatherNode, etc.)
    repository/               RouteRepository (offline-first)
  ui/
    theme/                    SlickTheme
    onboarding/               Staggered permission screens
    preflight/                Route config, convoy lobby, settings
    inflight/                 Zone1Header, Zone2Map, Zone3Deck
    survival/                 Text-only HUD
    tour/                     Tour planner, expense tracker
    components/               MassiveButton, TelemetryText
  util/                       Haversine, Result extensions, MetricConverter
```

## Orbit-MVI -- Unidirectional Data Flow

```kotlin
// ViewModel is a Container
class ConvoyViewModel @HiltViewModel constructor(
    private val repository: RouteRepository,
    private val meshManager: ConvoyMeshManager,
) : ViewModel(), ContainerHost<ConvoyState, ConvoySideEffect> {

    override val container = container<ConvoyState, ConvoySideEffect>(ConvoyState.Idle)

    fun onJoinConvoy(convoyId: String) = intent {
        reduce { state.copy(isConnecting = true) }
        val result = meshManager.joinConvoy(convoyId)
        result.onSuccess { reduce { state.copy(isConnecting = false, convoyId = convoyId) } }
        result.onFailure { postSideEffect(ConvoySideEffect.ShowError(it.message ?: "Unknown error")) }
    }
}
```

UI collects state via `collectAsState()`. Never mutates ViewModel state directly.

## File Size Limits

| Type | Max Lines | Action if Over |
|------|-----------|----------------|
| Activity / Service | 400 | Extract Engine components |
| Composable screen | 250 | Extract sub-composables |
| ViewModel | 300 | Extract use cases |
| Repository | 300 | Split by data source |
| Engine Manager | 400 | Extract strategy classes |
| Utility / Extension | 150 | Split by domain |
| Test file | 300 | Split by feature |
